# ---- VS Code: ignore personal state, commit shareable config ----
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# ---- Timebase i3X catalog ----
# Was gitignored to keep historian URLs out of the repo. Repo is
# private/internal-only, and the same hostname + IP are already
# in committed docker-compose.yml's extra_hosts, so catalog.yaml
# is committed too -- single source of truth, normal git pull /
# rebuild workflow, no per-env divergence. The file is bind-
# mounted at runtime (see docker-compose.yml volumes block) so
# post-deploy edits hot-swap on `docker compose restart api`
# rather than requiring an image rebuild.
